"{\"uid\": \"www.bostonglobe.com.-opinion-2016-06-28-brexit-was-referendum-what-means-british-3tkhiaiuio1dqkxtw0mrmi-story-html-Part1\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Britain is a country with an identity crisis.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 45, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is it still a world power, or is it just an American client state?\", \"from\": 46, \"to\": 112, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Is it European, or not?\", \"from\": 113, \"to\": 136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Are tolerance and multiculturalism defining civic virtues, or is it a country primarily for people with British blood - however that is defined?\", \"from\": 137, \"to\": 281, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last Thursday my wife, along with over 1,000 people representing 83 countries piled into a theater in Sacramento, Calif., to be sworn in as United States citizens.\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 446, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a celebration of the unity that can spring from difference.\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Later that day the United Kingdom, the country where I was born and raised, voted to leave the European Union, and in doing so rejected the exact sort of unity that my wife had just pledged to uphold.\", \"from\": 514, \"to\": 714, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a stark juxtaposition, and one that gets at the heart of the cultural crisis gripping the UK.\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week's vote shows just how fundamental those questions are.\", \"from\": 817, \"to\": 881, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brexit was meant to be a way for Prime Minister David Cameron to quiet a vocal faction of his Conservative Party that was deeply skeptical of a united Europe and enamored with a nostalgic vision of Britain's place in the world.\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Remaining in the EU should have been a slam dunk: Economists almost universally agreed that leaving would be a disaster for the economy.\", \"from\": 1110, \"to\": 1246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But for many in the United Kingdom, the European Union is not an economic body.\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1326, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is an organization that gives people from Southern and Eastern Europe unfettered access to British jobs and benefits.\", \"from\": 1327, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As the European Union struggled to solve the Syrian refugee crisis, and the Leave camp began to lean more heavily on an ugly, anti-immigrant message, the Brexit vote turned into a referendum on what it means to be British.\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1670, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And in that context, numbers never stood a change against nativism and nationalism.\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On June 23, a majority of the British public voted for a future that rejected immigrants and open borders in favor of inward-looking xenophobia.\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1899, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the clearest expression the British people have given since the end of the Second World War of what they think it means to be British.\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 2042, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was deeply troubling to see.\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2074, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertisement  But as much as the pro-Brexit camp would hate to admit it, leaving the European Union will do little to slow immigration.\", \"from\": 2076, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost 75 percent of net migration to Britain comes from outside the Eurozone.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bureaucrats in Brussels have no say in whether these people come to Britain or not.\", \"from\": 2292, \"to\": 2375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if cultural purity was a legitimate reason to enact public policy - and it is not - Brexit was a bad way of going about it.\", \"from\": 2376, \"to\": 2504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The United Kingdom will keep on indulging in this sort of toxic self-delusion until it realizes that identity and nationality are not the same thing.\", \"from\": 2506, \"to\": 2655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Globalization brings British culture out into the world just as in brings immigrants in.\", \"from\": 2656, \"to\": 2744, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the process, what it means to be British changes.\", \"from\": 2745, \"to\": 2797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sadiq Khan, the Pakistani-British mayor of London, is no less British than Boris Johnson, his predecessor as mayor and one of the most vocal advocates for leaving the Union.\", \"from\": 2798, \"to\": 2971, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thursday's vote did not change that.\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 3008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The British live in a nation of immigrants whether they like it or not.\", \"from\": 3009, \"to\": 3080, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whether your grandmother was born in Manchester has never been less relevant in determining whether you are British.\", \"from\": 3081, \"to\": 3197, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Brexit passed because a majority of voters bought into the idea that their country's future should look like a fairy-tale version of its past.\", \"from\": 3199, \"to\": 3341, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sad part is that they traded economic prosperity and global influence for a lie.\", \"from\": 3342, \"to\": 3426, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The future of Britain looks a lot like the swearing-in ceremony I saw in Sacramento - a group of people from all over the world trading in one nationality for the chance to live, work, and thrive in\", \"from\": 3427, \"to\": 3625, \"entities\": []}]}"